  "prompt": "Why was I blocked from adding questions on quora anonymously and how can I change it?",
  "response": "If you were blocked from adding questions anonymously on Quora, it could be due to several reasons:\n\n1. **Violation of Community Guidelines**: If your previous questions or activity have been flagged or reported for violating Quora's policies, your ability to post anonymously might be restricted.\n\n2. **Account Behavior**: If your account has exhibited behavior that Quora considers spammy or inappropriate, this could lead to restrictions.\n\n3. **Account Age or Reputation**: New accounts or those with low engagement may have limited capabilities until they establish a reputation within the community.\n\nTo resolve the issue and potentially regain the ability to ask questions anonymously, you can try the following steps:\n\n1. **Review Quora's Policies**: Familiarize yourself with Quora's community guidelines to ensure your future contributions align with their standards.\n\n2. **Improve Account Activity**: Engage positively on the platform by answering questions, upvoting good content, and participating in discussions. This can help build your reputation.\n\n3. **Contact Quora Support**: If you believe the restriction is a mistake, you can reach out to Quora's support team for clarification or to appeal the block.\n\n4. **Wait It Out**: Sometimes, restrictions might be temporary. Continuing to engage positively might help restore your privileges over time.\n\nMake sure to adhere to the platform's guidelines in the future to avoid similar issues.",
